1h or 2h, resists, pet strategies, strats vs. melee, what to expect from which class.</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#E5E5E6><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uotterantilles.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Otter Antilles</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>w4nn4b3!</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>4/3/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>10:59:59 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: An Idea.</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">go to castersrealm.com.<br>
<br>
There are a couple strategy guides for PvP somewhere in there that I used at one point in time.  The one thing I can't stress enough from a personal standpoint is resist gear/ac-hp gear.  In a melee fight you want ac-hp gear.  In a fight with casters you want resist (primarily MR) gear.<br>
<br>
vs SKs and Necros are the most difficult IMO.  If the SK waits awhile before using his HT... you may never get a chance for your LoH... so watch for that.  vs paladins make sure you manage your mana better than your opponent and bashes (shield) make a noticable difference.  With decent tactics and normal gear, you can beat almost any other class easily.  Don't even attempt a caster without arrows.  Stay away from Epic weapons unless you have yours or you're just asking for a beating.<br>
<br>
Otter Antilles<br>
Cavalier of The Shadow Order</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#D5D4D5><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/unibl.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nibl</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://nibl.homestead.com/files/annoyed.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>p0\/\/3r-p0sT3r!</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>4/4/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>4:10:48 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: An Idea.</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">I went to castersrealm and they repeated the same n00bie paladin duel method that only works against low MR duelers.<br>
<br>
&quot;You get the ultimate duel spell, flash of light... blah&quot;</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#E5E5E6><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uotterantilles.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Otter Antilles</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>w4nn4b3!</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>4/5/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>8:05:06 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: An Idea.</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Maybe they are newbie strats, but you have to learn the basics before you learn the advanced.  And as much as I hate to say it... the only way to learn the advanced is to learn how to read your opponent and beat his strategy.<br>
<br>
In general, I use 1hs/shield almost always.  The added AC and occasional well-timed stun can turn the fight your way in the long run.  Do NOT just continually hit bash/disarm unless you're toe-to-toe with a tank.<br>
<br>
I mainly use blind against pets and melees since it's really not as useful against casters.  And if you cast FoL 3 times and it's resisted... save your mana for something else.  My favorite FoL strat is to wait for an FoL to stick and then disarm.  Disarm is normally a joke, but mine seems to work in duels fairly well.  I've gone through a bubble of my opponents health sometimes before he realizes he was disarmed while he was blinded.<br>
<br>
Why are paladins in general more useful than SKs?  Because healing NEVER gets resisted.  If MR is a problem... use your mana to heal/buff yourself.  I would NOT suggest this against a class that can invis unless you have a way to see-invis because if you can't retarget a rogue or medding caster you can get in serious trouble.<br>
<br>
Anyway, practice makes perfect.  Just be able to handle your losses with grace and analyze all that happened.<br>
<br>
Otter</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#D5D4D5><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ucoramoor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Coramoor</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>The Valiant</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>4/5/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>11:44:39 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: An Idea.</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">i made a good guide to that on the paladin board once<br>
